File: From Wednesday, the price of unleaded 95 octane petrol is expected to fall to R16.03 per litre. JOHANNESBURG - Motorists will be paying 13 cents less for a litre of petrol and 5 cents less for diesel from midnight. The decrease is due to lower global crude oil prices. Unleaded 95 octane petrol currently costs R16.16 a litre. From Wednesday, this is expected to fall to R16.03 per litre.